column1: AA six-digit code is used for Foundation Foods in parentheses to distinguish items from Standard Reference legacy
BMeasurements below the LOD or RL are displayed as zero (0), with trace values between the LOD and LOQ reported as the detected iodine concentrations

CSee Documentation for reference details.  Abbreviations: FDA= Food and Drug Administration's Reference Amounts Customarily Consumed; USDA=USDA's SR Legacy (within USDA's FoodData Central database); FNDDS=Food and Nutrient Database for Dietary Studies (within USDA's FoodData Central database).
DDataset includes samples analyzed by the FDA's Center for Food Safety and Applied Nutrition laboratory in College Park, Maryland
*TDS and/or NDB identifiers with asterisks indicate products that differ from the generic product in that they contain iodate dough conditioners
1Omitted sample with value of 75 mcg I/seving as an outlier
3Grain products prepared without salt unless otherwise noted
4Omitted sample with 139 mcg I/serving– value probably from FD&C Red No. 3 food coloring
5Omitted 3 samples with values from 36 - 112 mcg I/serving – probably mixture of breads with and without iodate dough conditioners
6Omitted 6 samples with values from 65 - 210 mcg I/serving – probably mixture of breads with and without iodate dough conditioners
7Omitted 11 samples with values from 19 - 155 mcg I/serving – probably mixture of breads with and without iodate dough conditioners
8Omitted 10 samples with values from 55 - 145 mcg I/serving – probably mixture of breads with and without iodate dough conditioners
9Omitted sample with 100 mcg I/serving – value probably from FD&C Red No. 3 food coloring
10Omitted sample with 76 mcg I/serving – value probably from FD&C Red No. 3  food coloring
11Omitted 3 samples with 198 and 214 mcg I/serving – values probably from FD&C Red No. 3 food coloring
12Omitted 2 samples with 14 and 331 mcg I/serving – values probably from FD&C Red No. 3 food coloring
13Omitted 9 samples from 78 to 322 mcg I/serving – values probably from FD&C Red No. 3 food coloring
14Omitted sample with 545 mcg I/100g serving – value probably from FD&C Red No. 3 food coloring
15Omitted samples with values of 32 and 35 mcg I/serving – values may reflect the use of disinfectant during poultry cleaning, but we were unable to confirm this use
16Omitted sample with value of 520 mcg I/serving as an outlier, although value was confirmed by the lab
